## Description {#details}

This file defines late ObjC ARC optimizations.

ARC stands for Automatic Reference Counting and is a system for managing reference counts for objects in Objective C.

This specific file mainly deals with &#96;â€˜contracting`&#39; multiple lower level operations into singular higher level operations through pattern matching.

WARNING: This file knows about certain library functions. It recognizes them by name, and hardwires knowledge of their semantics.

WARNING: This file knows about how certain Objective-C library functions are used. Naive LLVM IR transformations which would otherwise be behavior-preserving may break these assumptions.

<Link id="l00311" /><CodeLine lineNumber="311"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Attempt to merge an objc&#95;release with a store, load, and objc&#95;retain to form</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00312" /><CodeLine lineNumber="312"><Highlight kind="comment">/// an objc&#95;storeStrong. An objc&#95;storeStrong:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00313" /><CodeLine lineNumber="313"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00314" /><CodeLine lineNumber="314"><Highlight kind="comment">///   objc&#95;storeStrong(i8&#42;&#42; %old&#95;ptr, i8&#42; new&#95;value)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00315" /><CodeLine lineNumber="315"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><Highlight kind="comment">/// is equivalent to the following IR sequence:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><Highlight kind="comment">///   ; Load old value.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319"><Highlight kind="comment">///   %old&#95;value = load i8&#42;&#42; %old&#95;ptr               (1)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00321" /><CodeLine lineNumber="321"><Highlight kind="comment">///   ; Increment the new value and then release the old value. This must occur</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00322" /><CodeLine lineNumber="322"><Highlight kind="comment">///   ; in order in case old&#95;value releases new&#95;value in its destructor causing</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00323" /><CodeLine lineNumber="323"><Highlight kind="comment">///   ; us to potentially have a dangling ptr.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00324" /><CodeLine lineNumber="324"><Highlight kind="comment">///   tail call i8&#42; @objc&#95;retain(i8&#42; %new&#95;value)    (2)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00325" /><CodeLine lineNumber="325"><Highlight kind="comment">///   tail call void @objc&#95;release(i8&#42; %old&#95;value)  (3)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00326" /><CodeLine lineNumber="326"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00327" /><CodeLine lineNumber="327"><Highlight kind="comment">///   ; Store the new&#95;value into old&#95;ptr</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00328" /><CodeLine lineNumber="328"><Highlight kind="comment">///   store i8&#42; %new&#95;value, i8&#42;&#42; %old&#95;ptr           (4)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00329" /><CodeLine lineNumber="329"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00330" /><CodeLine lineNumber="330"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The safety of this optimization is based around the following</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00331" /><CodeLine lineNumber="331"><Highlight kind="comment">/// considerations:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00332" /><CodeLine lineNumber="332"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00333" /><CodeLine lineNumber="333"><Highlight kind="comment">///  1 We are forming the store strong at the store. Thus to perform this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00334" /><CodeLine lineNumber="334"><Highlight kind="comment">///     optimization it must be safe to move the retain, load, and release to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00335" /><CodeLine lineNumber="335"><Highlight kind="comment">///     (4).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00336" /><CodeLine lineNumber="336"><Highlight kind="comment">///  2 We need to make sure that any re-orderings of (1), (2), (3), (4) are</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00337" /><CodeLine lineNumber="337"><Highlight kind="comment">///     safe.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00338" /><CodeLine lineNumber="338"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> ObjCARCContract::tryToContractReleaseIntoStoreStrong(</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00339" /><CodeLine lineNumber="339"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instruction">Instruction</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a239c4ac35d6028bfacaed4018d0488faab8e7b465df7c5979dc731d06e84ce2cf">Release</a>, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a0c27cc387928f22d241825cf0fb67ade">inst&#95;iterator</a> &amp;Iter,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="340"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/densemap">DenseMap&lt;BasicBlock &#42;, ColorVector&gt;</a> &amp;BlockColors) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="341"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// See if we are releasing something that we just loaded.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="342"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/spii/#ad2b7483c625986ac800ae1c31ae4cce7a5069619ca8fdce305534f3fe85091a0f">Load</a> = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a22eeee01734061ac1b31ccd994c49eef">dyn&#95;cast&lt;LoadInst&gt;</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/objcarc/#aa76bc27e7a62bc63263463a83525948f">GetArgRCIdentityRoot</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a239c4ac35d6028bfacaed4018d0488faab8e7b465df7c5979dc731d06e84ce2cf">Release</a>));</Highlight></CodeLine>
